📚 Subject: Computer Organization & Architecture (COA)
🧠 Topic: ALU, Datapath & Control Unit

1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)

The ALU is responsible for:

👉 Arithmetic operations:

Addition
Subtraction
Multiplication

👉 Logical operations:

AND, OR, NOT, XOR
🔹 ALU Inputs & Outputs

Inputs:

Operands (from registers)
Control signals

Output:

Result
Status flags
🔹 Status Flags (VERY IMPORTANT)

After ALU operation, flags are set:

Zero (Z) → Result = 0
Carry (C) → Carry generated
Sign (S) → Negative result
Overflow (V) → Overflow occurred

📌 Very common GATE questions.

🔹 Datapath

The datapath is the hardware path through which data flows.

Includes:

Registers
ALU
Multiplexers
Buses
🔹 Datapath Operation

1️⃣ Data fetched from registers
2️⃣ Sent to ALU
3️⃣ Operation performed
4️⃣ Result stored back

🔹 Control Unit (CU)

The Control Unit controls:

👉 Which operation to perform
👉 When to perform
👉 Data movement

🔹 Types of Control Unit
1️⃣ Hardwired Control
Uses fixed logic circuits
Faster
Difficult to modify
2️⃣ Microprogrammed Control
Uses control memory
Flexible
Slower

📌 GATE often asks comparison.

🔹 Control Signals

Examples:

Read / Write
ALU operation select
Register select
🔹 Datapath + Control = CPU

👉 Datapath → does work
👉 Control → directs work

🔹 Instruction Execution (Combined View)
Control unit fetches instruction
Decodes it
Sends signals
Datapath executes
ALU produces result
🔹 Common GATE Traps
Confusing ALU and CU roles
Forgetting flags meaning
Mixing hardwired vs microprogrammed
